choices.text:
not public transport

5 December 2013 at 4:05 pm

Whilst not supporting factors that encourage self medicating, it is the response that is more important as it is the piece of the jigsaw that will make all the difference as to whether the self medicating person will end up thriving or merely surviving their challenges.

Solidarity and genuine support should be the starting place and finding our own journey with by not being ‘reactive’ and by being ‘proactive’ we ensure we are all on the same page.

This allows everyone to stand in other people’s shoes and see the potential of limitless successes rather than limiting or excluding a life by peoples failures.

I agree.

Decades ago a visiting psychologist was quoted as saying when asked about Youth Suicide – “once our people lose the respect of other people, their own lives mean little or nothing to them.”
